content: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?> <metadata>  <idinfo>   <citation>    <citeinfo>     <origin>Sound GIS (data compilation)</origin>     <origin>Pacific Fishery Management Council</origin>     <origin>National Marine Fisheries Service, Northwest Region</origin>     <pubdate>200508</pubdate>     <title>700 fathom Depth Contour for Pacific Fishery Management Council's June 2005 Preferred Alternative, Groundfish EFH Final EIS</title>     <geoform>vector digital data</geoform>     <ftname Sync="TRUE">sde.DBO.Marine_EFHPrefAlt_700fm_ln_dd</ftname><onlink>http://marinehabitat.psmfc.org/gis-data.html</onlink><pubinfo><pubplace>Portland, OR</pubplace><publish>Pacific States Marine Fisheries Commission</publish></pubinfo></citeinfo>   </citation>   <descript>    <abstract>These data depict the primary 700 fathom isobath within the West Coast Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ).  The area to the west of this depth contour was designated by the Pacific Fishery Management Council on June 15, 2005 as part of the Preferred Alternative for the Groundfish Essential Fish Habitat (EFH), Final Environmental Impact Statement (FEIS).  In order to minimize adverse impacts to EFH, this area is proposed to be closed to fishing with bottom trawl.</abstract>    <purpose>These data were developed for the National Marine Fisheries Service Northwest Region and the Pacific Fishery Management Council in support of an Environmental Impact Statement (EIS) to consider the designation and conservation of Essential Fish Habitat (EFH) for Pacific Coast Groundfish.</purpose>    <supplinf>These areas are not legal boundaries.  They are conceptual representations of the areas designated by the Pacific Fishery Management Council as part of their Preferred Alterrnative for the Groundfish EFH Final EIS.  Legal boundaries will be developed through the proper Council and legal processes.</supplinf>    <langdata Sync="TRUE">en</langdata></descript>   <timeperd>    <timeinfo>     <sngdate>      <caldate>2005</caldate>     </sngdate>    </timeinfo>    <current>publication date</current>   </timeperd>   <status>    <progress>Complete</progress>    <update>None planned</update>   </status>   <spdom>    <bounding>     <westbc>-126.084301</westbc>     <eastbc>-118.172313</eastbc>     <northbc>48.122497</northbc>     <southbc>31.963684</southbc>    </bounding>    <lboundng><leftbc Sync="TRUE">-126.084301</leftbc><rightbc Sync="TRUE">-118.172313</rightbc><bottombc Sync="TRUE">31.963684</bottombc><topbc Sync="TRUE">48.122497</topbc></lboundng></spdom>   <keywords>    <theme>     <themekey>groundfish</themekey>     <themekey>essential fish habitat (EFH)</themekey>     <themekey>Final Environmental Impact Statement (EIS)</themekey>     <themekey>biota</themekey><themekey>oceans</themekey><themekey>environment</themekey><themekey>boundaries</themekey></theme>    <place>     <placekey>Washington</placekey>     <placekey>Oregon</placekey>     <placekey>California</placekey>     <placekey>west coast</placekey>     <placekey>Northwest Pacific Ocean</placekey>    </place>   </keywords>   <accconst>none</accconst>   <useconst>none</useconst>   <ptcontac>    <cntinfo>     <cntorgp>      <cntorg>Pacific Fishery Management Council</cntorg>     </cntorgp>     <cntaddr>      <addrtype>mailing and physical address</addrtype>      <address>7700 NE Ambassador Place, Suite 200</address>      <city>Portland</city>      <state>OR</state>      <postal>97220-1384</postal>      <country>U.S.A.</country>     </cntaddr>     <cntvoice>(503) 820-2280</cntvoice>     <cntfax>(503) 820-2299</cntfax>     <cntemail>pfmc.comments@noaa.gov</cntemail>    </cntinfo>   </ptcontac>   <native>Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 2; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.0.0.535</native>   <natvform Sync="TRUE">SDE Feature Class</natvform></idinfo>  <dataqual>   <attracc>    <attraccr>Because the line represents a single depth contour, no "substantive" attributes are contained in the shapefile, and therefore no accuracy assessment is needed.</attraccr>   </attracc>   <logic>The 700 fathom contour line was derived from the ETOPO2 data set (described in data sources), and the caveats associated with the source data would apply to this line.</logic>   <complete>The 700 fathom isobath is continuous and complete for the area between the northern and southern boundaries of of the west coast Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ)</complete>   <posacc>    <horizpa>     <horizpar>Absolute horizontal accuracy is unknown.  The 700 fathom depth contour was derived from ETOPO2 data, so the horizontal accuracy of this isobath will be consistent with the horizontal accuracy of that data set.   The source data are gridded into 2-minute lat/long cells, so the precision of the positions not extremely high.   A paper describing development of the ETOPO2 data set can be found at:  http://topex.ucsd.edu/marine_topo/text/topo.html.</horizpar>    </horizpa>   </posacc>   <lineage>    <srcinfo>     <srccite>      <citeinfo>       <origin>David T.
